text: Joseph Thewlis (born 1943), is a male former diver who competed for England. ==Diving career== Thewlis was a National junior champion before representing England in the 3 metres springboard, at the 1970 British Commonwealth Games in Edinburgh, Scotland. ==References== Category:1943 births Category:English male divers Category:Divers at the 1970 British Commonwealth Games Category:Living people
title: Joseph Thewlis
